title: Australian dollar down as commodities plummet
text:
China’s economy grew at its slowest pace for six years.
AAP THE Australian dollar has edged lower as commodities took a hit following the release of weak Chinese industrial production data.
At 0630 AEDT on Tuesday, the currency was trading at 72.52 US cents, down from 72.73 cents on Monday.
Monday’s data showed that China’s economy grew in the third quarter at its slowest pace for six years, and commodities nosedived with the Thomson Reuters/Core Commodity CRB commodity index down 1.1 per cent.
CURRENCY SNAPSHOT AT 0630 AEDT ON TUESDAY
One Australian dollar buys:
* 72.52 US cents, from 72.73 cents on Tuesday
* 86.66 Japanese yen, from 86.77 yen
* 64.05 euro cents, from 63.98 euro cents
(*Currency closes taken at 1700 AEDT previous local session)
Source: IRESS
